{"model": "Qwen 3.5 35B-A3B (MoE)", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "logic_ages__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 512.8, "generation_tps": 78.9, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 19.8, "output": "Let's define the variables for the current ages of Alice and Bob.\nLet $A$ be Alice's current age.\nLet $B$ be Bob's current age.\n\nStep 1: Translate the first statement into an equation.\n\"Alice is twice as old as Bob\" means:\n$$A = 2B$$\n\nStep 2: Translate the second statement into an equation.\n\"In 10 years, Alice will be 1.5 times as old as Bob\".\nIn 10 years, Alice's age will be $A + 10$.\nIn 10 years, Bob's age will be $B + 10$.\nSo, the equation is:\n$$A + 10 = 1.5(B + 10)$$\n\nStep 3: Substitute the first equation into the second equation.\nSince $A = 2B$, replace $A$ in the second equation:\n$$2B + 10 = 1.5(B + 10)$$\n\nStep 4: Solve for $B$.\nExpand the right side of the equation:\n$$2B + 10 = 1.5B + 15$$\n\nSubtract $1.5B$ from both sides:\n$$2B - 1.5B + 10 = 15$$\n$$0.5B + 10 = 15$$\n\nSubtract 10 from both sides:\n$$0.5B = 5$$\n\nDivide by 0.5 (which is the same as multiplying by 2):\n$$B = 10$$\n\nStep 5: Verify the answer.\nIf Bob is 10, Alice is $2 \\times 10 = 20$.\nIn 10 years, Bob will be 20 and Alice will be 30.\nIs 30 equal to 1.5 times 20?\n$$1.5 \\times 20 = 30$$\nThe condition holds true.\n\nANSWER: 10", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "a33ec0efd7f9"}
