{"model": "Qwen 3.5 35B-A3B (MoE)", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "math_combinatorics__t3_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 442.6, "generation_tps": 79.1, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 10.1, "output": "To find the number of ways to choose 3 items from a set of 7, we use the combination formula, which is denoted as $\\binom{n}{k}$ or $C(n, k)$. The formula is:\n\n$$ \\binom{n}{k} = \\frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!} $$\n\nHere, $n = 7$ (the total number of items) and $k = 3$ (the number of items to choose).\n\n1.  Substitute the values into the formula:\n    $$ \\binom{7}{3} = \\frac{7!}{3!(7-3)!} $$\n\n2.  Simplify the denominator:\n    $$ \\binom{7}{3} = \\frac{7!}{3!4!} $$\n\n3.  Expand the factorials. Note that $7! = 7 \\times 6 \\times 5 \\times 4!$:\n    $$ \\binom{7}{3} = \\frac{7 \\times 6 \\times 5 \\times 4!}{3! \\times 4!} $$\n\n4.  Cancel out the $4!$ terms:\n    $$ \\binom{7}{3} = \\frac{7 \\times 6 \\times 5}{3!} $$\n\n5.  Calculate $3!$ (which is $3 \\times 2 \\times 1 = 6$) and simplify further:\n    $$ \\binom{7}{3} = \\frac{7 \\times 6 \\times 5}{6} $$\n\n6.  Cancel out the $6$:\n    $$ \\binom{7}{3} = 7 \\times 5 = 35 $$\n\nANSWER: 35", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "0906c375ac54"}
