{"model": "Qwen 3.5 35B-A3B (MoE)", "runtime": "llamacpp", "prompt_name": "math_multiply__t2_cot", "prompt_tokens": 0, "generation_tokens": 0, "prompt_tps": 428.9, "generation_tps": 78.0, "peak_memory_gb": 0.0, "wall_time_sec": 25.2, "output": "To calculate $47 \\times 89$, we can break the multiplication down into parts.\n\n**Step 1:** Break 89 into $80 + 9$.\n$$47 \\times 89 = 47 \\times (80 + 9)$$\n\n**Step 2:** Multiply 47 by 9.\n$$47 \\times 9 = (40 \\times 9) + (7 \\times 9)$$\n$$40 \\times 9 = 360$$\n$$7 \\times 9 = 63$$\n$$360 + 63 = 423$$\n\n**Step 3:** Multiply 47 by 80.\n$$47 \\times 80 = (47 \\times 8) \\times 10$$\n$$47 \\times 8 = (40 \\times 8) + (7 \\times 8)$$\n$$40 \\times 8 = 320$$\n$$7 \\times 8 = 56$$\n$$320 + 56 = 376$$\n$$376 \\times 10 = 3760$$\n\n**Step 4:** Add the results from Step 2 and Step 3 together.\n$$423 + 3760$$\n$$3 + 0 = 3$$\n$$2 + 6 = 8$$\n$$4 + 7 = 11$$ (write 1, carry 1)\n$$3 + 1 = 4$$\n$$Total = 4183$$\n\nAlternatively, using the distributive property with subtraction:\n$$47 \\times 89 = 47 \\times (90 - 1)$$\n$$47 \\times 90 = 4230$$\n$$47 \\times 1 = 47$$\n$$4230 - 47 = 4183$$\n\nANSWER: 4183", "error": null, "prompt_hash": "f2fc3608f651"}
